data.value:
Help for Bitmap Clouder:
  Command Line:
    {0} {1}
    {0} {2}
    {0} {3} [{4}{5}] [{6}] [{7}]

    {1}	prints this
    {2}	prints the license
    {3}	input file
    {4}	specifies to blur {4} times
    {5}	times to blur
    {6}	output file
    {7}	opens {3}

    If {4} is not specified, 1 is used for {5}.
    If {6} is not specified, {8} is used.

  Return Values:
    0 - Okay
    1 - No arguments
    2 - Couldn't parse {5}
    3 - {5} was not positive.
    4 - Couldn't find {3}
    5 - Couldn't read {3}
    6 - {3} is empty.
    7 - {3} is not a valid bitmap.
    8 - Couldn't save to {6}
    9 - Couldn't open {5}
